Damyean Da'Kethe Dotson (born May 6, 1994) is an American basketball player. He was selected with the 44th pick of the 2017 NBA Draft by the New York Knicks.

He played two seasons for the University of Oregon. After his sophomore season, he was dismissed due to sexual assault allegations, though he was never charged due to a lack of evidence and conflicting statements made by the victim. [1] He transferred to the University of Houston. As a senior, he averaged 17.4 points and 6.9 rebounds per game and was named to the First Team American Athletic Conference.[2]
